GROUP 10 - COCA COLA STOCKS DATASET¶

Introduction¶

In this notebook you will implement the regression algorithm: Linear Regression:

  • Dataset description: This dataset contains information about Coca Cola company stocks from 2012 to 2022

Below is a list of sections.¶

    1. Data Pre-Processing
    1. Building the model
    1. Make prediction

2. Building the model¶

  • After preprocessing the data, we will proceed to build the model.
In [29]:
x = df['Open']
y = df['Close']
plt.scatter(x,y)
plt.show()
In [31]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
est = LinearRegression(fit_intercept=True)
x=df[['Open']]
y=df[['Close']]
est.fit(x,y)
print("The cofficient(s) a is(are)",est.coef_)
print("The intercept b is", est.intercept_)

The cofficient(s) a is(are) [[0.99860318]]
The intercept b is [0.06809476]
In [33]:
x=df['Open']
y=df['Close']
sns.regplot(x=x, y=y, line_kws={'color': 'red', 'linewidth': 2}, label='Red Line')


equation = '$\\hat{y}$=' + str(est.coef_[0][0]) + 'x+' + str(est.intercept_[0])

plt.annotate(equation, xy=(4.5,2.8))

plt.show()
In [35]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
testperc=0.2
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = testperc, random_state = 42)
est = LinearRegression(fit_intercept=True)
est.fit(pd.DataFrame(X_train),pd.DataFrame(y_train))
print("The cofficient(s) a is(are)",est.coef_)
print("The intercept b is", est.intercept_)

The cofficient(s) a is(are) [[0.99874218]]
The intercept b is [0.054809]
